Stocks of the following companies
may have unusual price changes in Taipei trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses, and prices are as of the last close.    Taiwan â€™s Taiex Index fell 226.70, or 2.6 percent, to
8,609.86.    AU Optronics Corp . (2409 TT): AUO Crystal Corp. plans to
start production at a solar wafer plant in Taiwan in the fourth
quarter, parent AU Optronics said in an e-mailed statement Feb.
11. The first phase of the project will have an annual capacity
of 300 megawatts of ingots and wafers, the Hsinchu, Taiwan-based
company said. AU Optronics declined 2.6 percent to NT$26.30.    ProMOS Technologies Inc . (5387 TT): The memory-chip company
is in talks with the Taiwanese government and its banks about
waiving some of its debt to meet a condition stipulated by
Elpida Memory Inc. for a potential merger, the Yomiuri newspaper
reported, without saying where it got the information. ProMOS
slipped 1.9 percent to NT$2.09.  To contact the reporter on this story:
